 43 adult patients with dumping syndrome received pasireotide s.

c.

 during the dose escalation phase (3 months dose could be increased based on the presence of hypoglycemia during OGTT).

 After completing Month 3, patients were switched to pasireotide LAR for 3 months (up to Month 6).

 The core phase of the study was completed at the end of Month 6.

 Patients were allowed to enter the 6 month extension phase if they experienced benefit with pasireotide LAR treatment.

